  "body": "In [some applications](https://github.com/medvedev1088/ethereum-etl) where performance is important it's convenient to query all receipts in a block in a single request. \r\n\r\nSince receipts are part of a block, as defined in the yellowpaper, it makes sense to allow including them in the block response for [eth_getBlockByHash](https://github.com/ethereum/wiki/wiki/JSON-RPC#eth_getblockbyhash) and [eth_getBlockByNumber](https://github.com/ethereum/wiki/wiki/JSON-RPC#eth_getblockbynumber) by adding the boolean parameter to the request:\r\n\r\n> Parameters\r\n> - QUANTITY|TAG - integer of a block number, or the string \"earliest\", \"latest\" or \"pending\", as in the default block parameter.\r\n> - Boolean - If true it returns the full transaction objects, if false only the hashes of the transactions.\r\n> - **Boolean - If true it returns the full receipts objects, if false the receipts objects are not returned.**\r\n\r\nHere is an analogous issue for parity https://github.com/paritytech/parity-ethereum/issues/9075",
